inputs.description: A collection of arguments for invoking getDomainName.

domainName.description: Fully-qualified domain name to look up. If no domain name is found, an error will be returned.

tags.description: Key-value map of tags for the resource.

outputs.description: A collection of values returned by getDomainName.

arn.description: ARN of the found custom domain name.

certificateArn.description: ARN for an AWS-managed certificate that is used by edge-optimized endpoint for this domain name.

certificateName.description: Name of the certificate that is used by edge-optimized endpoint for this domain name.

certificateUploadDate.description: Upload date associated with the domain certificate.

cloudfrontDomainName.description: Hostname created by Cloudfront to represent the distribution that implements this domain name mapping.

cloudfrontZoneId.description: For convenience, the hosted zone ID (`Z2FDTNDATAQYW2`) that can be used to create a Route53 alias record for the distribution.

endpointConfigurations.description: List of objects with the endpoint configuration of this domain name.

id.description: The provider-assigned unique ID for this managed resource.

regionalCertificateArn.description: ARN for an AWS-managed certificate that is used for validating the regional domain name.

regionalCertificateName.description: User-friendly name of the certificate that is used by regional endpoint for this domain name.

regionalDomainName.description: Hostname for the custom domain's regional endpoint.

regionalZoneId.description: Hosted zone ID that can be used to create a Route53 alias record for the regional endpoint.

securityPolicy.description: Security policy for the domain name.

tags.description: Key-value map of tags for the resource.
